OL,3,C'Crucial' railway line reopens as
OL,4,Csignalling upgrade programme concludes
OL,6,FNetwork Rail has spent #61million
OL,7,Fmodernising the signal systems in
OL,8,FCarlisle, which dated back to the
OL,9,F1960s. The newer technology should,
OL,10,Faccording to Network Rail, make
OL,11,Fjourneys on the West Coast Mainline
OL,12,Fmore reliable.
OL,14,FThe upgrade work began in April 2025,
OL,15,Fand saw a range of improvements
OL,16,Fcarried out including new detection
OL,17,Fsystems to monitor train movements,
OL,18,Fupgrades to tracks and points, and an
OL,19,Foverhaul of signalling power supplies.
